active_products_inventory_info_message: All active products in your company including non-saleable. Variants/Boxes are not treated as distinct products in this context.
vendors_inventory_info_message: All vendor profiles created by your company across all locations, irrespective of whether they are currently active or inactive.
expiring_batch_stats_product_value_messa: If no cost price is specified, the system will use 0 as the value for that particular product.
expiring_batch_stats_potential_profit_me: Probable profit value of expiring items. In the absence of a specified cost price, it will display the selling price of the product. The calculation involves subtracting the cost price from the sale price. If the selling price is not defined, it will result in a negative profit. This calculation includes VAT.
dead_inventory_title_info_message: "Dead inventory" refers to items that are no longer selling or generating revenue, often due to obsolescence or low demand. It can also be termed as "obsolete inventory" or "dead stock." Managing dead inventory is crucial to optimize resources and prevent financial losses. This calculation includes VAT.
dead_inventory_value_profit_info_message: If no cost price is specified, the system will consider 0 value for the product. For the profit percentage of dead items, in the absence of a specified cost price, it will display the selling price, with the calculation involving subtracting the cost price (or 0 if unspecified) from the sale price. If the selling price is not defined, the result will indicate a negative profit, with the calculation including VAT.
lost_damaged_inventory_info_message: Encompasses losses, damages, discrepancies, theft, or any form of inventory reduction.
lost_inventory_profit_value_message: If no cost price is specified, the system will consider 0 value for that particular product. For the profit percentage of damaged/reduced inventory items, in the absence of a specified cost price, it will display the selling price, with the calculation involving subtracting the cost price (or 0 if unspecified) from the sale price. If the selling price is not defined, the result will indicate a negative profit, with the calculation including VAT.
out_of_stock_inventory_message: If the stock for an inventory managed product reaches zero or goes negative, it will be displayed here on the card. Products marked with 'Out of stock' explicity aren't considered here.
low_stock_inventory_message: When the stock level of a product managed in the inventory reaches the threshold specified in "Low Stock," it will be taken into account for the calculation.
